    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-06-01T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-06-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="720"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d720">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.111/77.]</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Port au Prince</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-06-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 1, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The stores of Ottoman Syrians, and those of Syrians of other nationalities who
                    have not received licenses, were officially closed to-day. <pb facs="0656"
                        n="540" xml:id="pg_540"/> Two Americans were affected by this action, but
                    the Haitian Government yesterday promised that their stores would not be closed
                    and it is probable that adjustment in regard to them can be made.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Furniss</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
